title: The Beginner's Handbook of Amateur Radio
description:
The Beginner's Handbook of Amateur Radio


English | Pages: 448| PDF | 2.6 mb


Essential A-to-Z Ham Radio Guide The revised edition of the most trusted guide in ham radio is here just in time to help you pass the new No-Code Technician Class exams! Used by thousands of ham operators to set up their first shortwave transmitters and to get their licenses, Clay Laster's Beginner's Handbook of Amateur Radio, Fourth Edition delivers all the guidance you need -- from radio and electronics fundamentals needed to set up a transmitter
